data.description: Looking for the benefits of country living while being minutes to all major amenities? Check out this amazing 10-acre property, with a shed, separate detached garage and a barn with a loft. Enjoy the gorgeous oak trees and a gas fire pit for those beautiful evening gatherings. This property is completely fenced with cross fencing and zoned AG so bring your horses, RV, boat, ATV's...no restrictions! The brick ranch style home sits on a paved road and is just minutes to the Suncoast Parkway with new plans for the Veterans Express extension. This 3 bedroom, almost 2000 sq ft home features a circular driveway, new tile throughout, a huge kitchen with newer cabinets, granite counters and a closet pantry, spacious living room with wood-burning fireplace, master bath with newer shower and vanity, separate room used as a man cave can easily be another bedroom, inside laundry room includes washer & dryer. Step out through the sliders leading to the back with stone walkway.  Needs some updating so come envision your new beginning while it's still available! NO HOA. Veterans Memorial Park, and Anderson Snow Park, popular for its sports complex and play area are less than 5 miles away. Crews Lake Park adjoins the home, known for its beautiful camping sites and picturesque scenery. Lots of shopping and local favorite dining options nearby. Minutes to the famous Weeki Wachee live mermaids, Pine Island Park and Roger's Park for fun on the water. Close to the Suncoast parkway for quick access to the airport, Tampa, Clearwater and St. Pete Beaches (Ranked in the top 5 Beaches in the US), also close to the famous Tarpon Springs Sponge Docks. Seller is open to reasonable offers knowing house needs TLC. Seller states the 10 acres can be sub-divided.
